('tpl-contract-v1', 'Standard Service Agreement', 'contract', E'SERVICE AGREEMENT\nGraviss Marketing, LLC & [CLIENT NAME]\n\nThis Service Agreement ("Agreement") is entered into as of the date of last signature below, by and between:\n\nClient: [CLIENT NAME] ("Client")\nService Provider: Graviss Marketing, LLC ("Service Provider")\nPrepared by: Jonathan P. Graviss\n\n1. Scope of Services\n\nGraviss Marketing agrees to perform the following services for [CLIENT NAME] as outlined in the approved proposal dated [PROPOSAL DATE]. Services are described below.\n\n[SERVICE 1 — e.g., Website Development]\n[DESCRIPTION OF SERVICE AND DELIVERABLES.]\n* [Deliverable]\n* [Deliverable]\n* [Deliverable]\n\n[SERVICE 2 — e.g., SEO / Ongoing Management]\n[DESCRIPTION OF SERVICE AND DELIVERABLES.]\n* [Deliverable]\n* [Deliverable]\n* [Deliverable]\n\n[SERVICE 3 — if applicable]\n[DELETE IF NOT APPLICABLE.]\n\nOptional Ongoing Services (Post-Launch)\nThe following services are not included in the base agreement and may be elected by the Client at any time via written confirmation:\n\n[OPTIONAL SERVICE 1] — $[AMOUNT]/month\n[Brief description of what is included.]\n\n[OPTIONAL SERVICE 2] — $[AMOUNT]/month\n[Brief description of what is included.]\n\n2. Investment\n\n[PAYMENT COMPONENT 1 — e.g., One-Time Fee]\n[SERVICE NAME]: $[AMOUNT] — [Due Upon Signing / Paid in Full / Net 15]\n[PAYMENT TERMS AND CONDITIONS. Include deposit structure if applicable.]\n\n| Payment | Amount | Trigger |\n|---------|--------|---------|\n| [Upon Agreement Execution] | $[AMOUNT] | [50% deposit to initiate work] |\n| [Prior to Delivery / Upon Completion] | $[AMOUNT] | [Balance due before deployment] |\n\n[PAYMENT COMPONENT 2 — e.g., Monthly Retainer]\n[SERVICE NAME]: $[AMOUNT]/month\n[DESCRIBE BILLING CYCLE — e.g., billed on the 1st of each month, auto-pay, etc.]\n\n3. Timeline\n\n* Work commences [immediately upon execution / on DATE] upon execution of this Agreement\n* [MILESTONE 1] delivered by [DATE]\n* [MILESTONE 2] delivered by [DATE]\n* [MILESTONE 3 / LAUNCH] targeted for [DATE / timeline contingent on content delivery]\n* Graviss Marketing will communicate proactively if any milestone is at risk\n\n4. Client Responsibilities\n\n[CLIENT NAME] agrees to:\n* Provide Graviss Marketing with access to [WEBSITE / CMS / GOOGLE ACCOUNTS / DOMAIN] within [NUMBER] business days of Agreement execution\n* [COMPLETE QUESTIONNAIRE / PROVIDE BRAND ASSETS / SUPPLY CONTENT] by [DATE / within X business days]\n* Respond to review requests, approvals, and information requests in a timely manner\n* [ADDITIONAL CLIENT OBLIGATION]\n* [ADDITIONAL CLIENT OBLIGATION]\n\n5. [INCLUDED PACKAGE — e.g., 90-Day Maintenance Period / if applicable]\n\n[DESCRIBE ANY COMPLIMENTARY OR INCLUDED PERIOD OF SERVICE POST-LAUNCH. DELETE IF NOT APPLICABLE.]\n\nAt the conclusion of the [X]-day period, both parties will evaluate and formally establish the ongoing monthly rate. Neither party is obligated to continue beyond this period without a separate written agreement.\n\n6. Intellectual Property\n\nUpon receipt of full payment, [CLIENT NAME] owns all deliverables produced under this Agreement. Graviss Marketing retains the right to reference this engagement in general marketing and portfolio materials without disclosing confidential Client information.\n\n7. Confidentiality\n\nBoth parties agree to maintain the confidentiality of any proprietary business, financial, or operational information shared during this engagement and not to disclose such information to third parties without prior written consent.\n\n8. No Guarantee of Results\n\nGraviss Marketing will apply industry best practices across all deliverables. However, Graviss Marketing does not guarantee specific search engine rankings, traffic levels, lead volume, or revenue outcomes. Results are subject to factors outside the control of either party including search engine algorithm updates, platform limitations, and market conditions.\n\n9. Limitation of Liability\n\nGraviss Marketing''s total liability under this Agreement shall not exceed the total fees paid by the Client under this Agreement. In no event shall either party be liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.\n\n10. Termination\n\nEither party may terminate this Agreement with [30] days written notice. In the event of termination:\n* If termination occurs before work commences, the Client is entitled to a full refund of any deposit paid\n* If termination occurs after work has commenced, fees will be prorated based on work completed; no refund will be issued for completed work\n* [ADDITIONAL TERMINATION TERMS IF APPLICABLE]\n\n11. Governing Law\n\nThis Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Florida, without regard to its conflict of law provisions. Any disputes arising under this Agreement shall be resolved in a court of competent jurisdiction in the State of Florida.\n\n12. Amendments\n\nAny modifications to this Agreement must be made in writing and signed by both parties. Verbal agreements or email confirmations do not constitute amendments to this Agreement unless formalized through a written addendum.\n\n13. Entire Agreement\n\nThis Agreement constitutes the entire understanding between the parties with respect to its subject matter and supersedes all prior proposals, discussions, or representations, written or oral.\n\nSignatures\n\nBy signing below, both parties agree to the full terms of this Agreement.\n\nGraviss Marketing, LLC\nSignature: ___________________________\nName: Jonathan P. Graviss\nTitle: Chief Executive Officer\nDate: ___________________________\n\n[CLIENT NAME]\nSignature: ___________________________\nName: ___________________________\nTitle: ___________________________\nDate: ___________________________', 1, true),

