('tpl-addendum-v1', 'Standard Contract Addendum', 'addendum', E'CONTRACT ADDENDUM — CHANGE OF SCOPE\nGraviss Marketing, LLC & [CLIENT NAME]\n\nThis Addendum ("Addendum") is entered into as of the date of last signature below and is incorporated into and made part of the original Service Agreement between the parties dated [ORIGINAL AGREEMENT DATE] ("Original Agreement"). All terms of the Original Agreement remain in full force and effect except as expressly modified herein.\n\nClient: [CLIENT NAME] ("Client")\nService Provider: Graviss Marketing, LLC ("Service Provider")\nPrepared by: Jonathan P. Graviss\n\n1. Purpose of Addendum\n\nThe parties have agreed to expand the scope of the Original Agreement to include [BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF NEW SCOPE]. This functionality/service was not included in the original [ORIGINAL SCOPE NAME] and constitutes a material change in [development / service / delivery] requirements warranting a formal change of scope agreement.\n\n2. Background & Context\n\n[1–2 SENTENCES DESCRIBING WHY THIS CHANGE OF SCOPE IS NEEDED. Reference the original engagement and what has changed or evolved.]\n\n[DESCRIBE THE NEW SCOPE AT A HIGH LEVEL — what it is, what problem it solves, and how it fits into the broader engagement.]\n\n3. Additional Scope of Work\n\n[SCOPE TITLE]\nGraviss Marketing will [DESCRIBE WHAT WILL BE BUILT / DELIVERED].\n\n[DELIVERABLE CATEGORY 1]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n\n[DELIVERABLE CATEGORY 2]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n\n[DELIVERABLE CATEGORY 3 — Technical Implementation]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n* [Deliverable detail]\n\n4. Launch Sequencing [DELETE IF NOT APPLICABLE]\n\nThis expanded scope will [not delay / replace / augment] the [EXISTING DELIVERABLE / LAUNCH]. Graviss Marketing and [CLIENT NAME] agree that:\n* [EXISTING MILESTONE] will proceed on its existing schedule without dependency on this Addendum''s deliverables\n* [NEW SCOPE] will be developed in a separate build cycle and delivered upon completion\n* Graviss Marketing will provide a dedicated timeline following [TRIGGER EVENT]\n\n5. Additional Investment\n\n[SCOPE TITLE] Fee: $[AMOUNT] ([One-Time / Monthly])\n\n| Payment | Amount | Trigger |\n|---------|--------|---------|\n| Upon Addendum Execution | $[AMOUNT] | [50% deposit to initiate scope] |\n| Prior to Delivery | $[AMOUNT] | [Balance due before completion and deployment] |\n\nNo deliverables will be deployed until payment has been received and confirmed in full. This fee is separate from and in addition to the fees established in the Original Agreement.\n\n6. Client Responsibilities\n\nIn connection with this expanded scope, [CLIENT NAME] agrees to:\n* [PROVIDE SPECIFIC CONTENT / ASSETS / ACCESS]\n* [DEFINE AND CONFIRM SCOPE PARAMETERS PRIOR TO DEVELOPMENT]\n* [PROVIDE TIMELY FEEDBACK AND APPROVALS]\n* [ADDITIONAL OBLIGATION]\n\n[CLIENT NAME] acknowledges that delays in providing required materials will impact delivery timeline. Graviss Marketing is not liable for delays resulting from incomplete or late information delivery.\n\n7. Intellectual Property\n\nUpon receipt of full payment, [CLIENT NAME] owns all deliverables produced under this Addendum. Graviss Marketing retains the right to reference this engagement in general portfolio and marketing materials without disclosing proprietary or confidential Client information.\n\n8. Ongoing Management\n\n[DELIVERABLE], once launched, will fall under the existing [$AMOUNT]/month ongoing management retainer established in the Original Agreement. [DESCRIBE WHAT IS AND IS NOT INCLUDED WITHIN THE EXISTING RETAINER SCOPE.]\n\nSignificant changes, new features, or additions beyond the original build will be scoped and priced separately.\n\n[DELETE THIS SECTION IF NO ONGOING RETAINER EXISTS.]\n\n9. Effect on Original Agreement\n\nExcept as expressly set forth in this Addendum, all terms, conditions, payment structures, intellectual property provisions, confidentiality obligations, governing law, and dispute resolution procedures of the Original Agreement dated [ORIGINAL AGREEMENT DATE] remain unchanged and in full force and effect. This Addendum is incorporated into and forms part of the Original Agreement.\n\n10. Governing Law\n\nThis Addendum shall be governed by the laws of the State of Florida, consistent with the Original Agreement.\n\nSignatures\n\nBy signing below, both parties agree to the expanded scope and additional investment outlined in this Addendum.\n\nGraviss Marketing, LLC\nSignature: ___________________________\nName: Jonathan P. Graviss\nTitle: Chief Executive Officer\nDate: ___________________________\n\n[CLIENT NAME]\nSignature: ___________________________\nName: ___________________________\nTitle: ___________________________\nDate: ___________________________', 1, true)

